        "testimonial_HyGpCE": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "The trip was amazing, man. I live in northern BC, Fort Nelson, a couple hours’ drive and 5 of our horses. 20 km trip into base camp, and day rides from there. 9 days on horses, 180+ km between boots and horseback. On the 7th day I shot my ram.The knife was amazing. My dad had his Havalon and I had my Kestrel. His Havalon handle snapped on him, and we finished the caping with my Kestrel",
            "author": "Matt Parker",
            "author_image": "shopify://shop_images/WhatsApp_Image_2025-09-29_at_22.06.11_8d81e47e.png",
            "object_fit": "contain",
            "object_position": "center"
          }
        },
        "testimonial_N6iVk9": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "Being a professional guide and a son of a ranch butcher, I've skinned a lot of animals and a knife that can hold a sharp edge is a must. I've used many brands of knives and Kestrel Knives are the only one I've found that can hold a sharp edge the longest. I bought my first EDC about 3 years ago and skinned 2 elk and a 1,200 lbs buffalo with it so far and still haven't had to use my wet stone to resharpen it.",
            "author": "Latigo Hext",
            "author_image": "shopify://shop_images/latigo.png",
            "object_fit": "cover",
            "object_position": "bottom"
          }
        },
        "testimonial_LPHqbg": {
