        "testimonial_7eRwNm": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "Kodiak ended with a billy goat, two Sitka Blacktail deer and a caribou. All dressed with the kestrel ultralighter in my hands. It does take some getting used to but once you understand how the knife works it cuts like butter and stays sharp... I only touched up the knife once with a field sharpening kit from Nathan after three animals and only because I wanted to try the sharpening kit. To my surprise I worked well fleshing out hides as well as cutting through meat.I use this knife all the time now, from cutting rope, meat, hides, vegetables, cardboard and whatever else happens to need severing.This is a great knife that's extremely light and stays sharp and will stay on my pack on all my future hunts.",
            "author": "Jon C. ",
            "author_image": "shopify://shop_images/jon_c.png",
            "object_fit": "cover",
            "object_position": "center"
          }
        },
        "testimonial_UDqLdD": {
          "type": "testimonial",
