            "object_position": "center"
          }
        },
        "testimonial_FMFEzz": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "What a great knife. These are the lightest weight knives I’ve ever seen and truly a necessity for the backcountry hunter.",
            "author": "Chris C.",
            "author_image": "shopify://shop_images/chris_c.png",
            "object_fit": "cover",
            "object_position": "center"
          }
        },
        "testimonial_N8X9hR": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "Just a quick note of thanks and to rave about my experience using your knives.  We’ve gone through sheep, caribou and countless whitetails using various models all with outstanding results.  The design and function are flawless and the emphasis on weight has made them a big hit as gifts for several guides along my travels.  And scary sharp, got a few scars to attest to this fact. Can’t tell you how much I appreciate the craftsmanship and service.",
            "author": "Customer for life.",
            "author_image": "shopify://shop_images/customer.png",
            "object_fit": "cover",
            "object_position": "center"
          }
        },
        "testimonial_a7pVRd": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "Used my Kestrel knife on my antelope buck. This is the third animal that I’ve used the knife on and it works awesome. It’s so light and thin you don’t even know it’s in your pack. The other thing I really like is that it’s so simple…no folding mechanism or blades to cut yourself on while changing them out (Havalon!) but enough mass behind the blade to really carve against bone, pry with, or whatever. Kestrel has it figured out…simple, effective, light, and cutting edge (pun intended)",
            "author": "David Hamilton Vortex Optics",
            "author_image": "shopify://shop_images/david.png",
            "object_fit": "cover",
            "object_position": "center"
          }
        },
        "testimonial_gA7QJj": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "I’ve had these knives forever and they’re perfect to carry along in the mountains.",
            "author": "Kyle Brundage",
            "author_image": "shopify://shop_images/kyle_brundage.png",
            "object_fit": "cover",
            "object_position": "center"
          }
        },
        "testimonial_48jm4P": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "I heard about Kestrel knives from Jason @ Kuiu and called him to see what he had to offer. After he sent me a titanium ultra light knife to look at, I immediately ordered several of them. I used it on a recent Stone sheep hunt in BC and it was wonderful and unbelievably lightweight. It retained its edge through the dressing and full body caping and is still sharp enough for several more. I had taken a couple of other kestrels with me and gave them to my guide and wrangler. They loved the feel and weight and the way the knife kept its edge.I've since ordered several more and will be passing them out around the world. Thanks Nate for a great knife and great customer interaction!!!!",
            "author": "Tom ",
            "author_image": "shopify://shop_images/tom_9d07f0c1-5fce-4944-92d1-3035c82b0548.png",
            "object_fit": "cover",
            "object_position": "center"
          }
        },
        "testimonial_Xmw7YB": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "I’ve owned an Ovis Hunter for years (10+ I think) and it’s a great knife. It holds an edge and sharpens easily, it’s bombproof, and it fits so well in my hand even when it’s covered in blood, dirt, and guts. It’s been with me on all my elk, deer, bear, and moose hunts all over North America and even on fishing trips. It’s gutted, skinned, butchered, deboned, and quartered many animals and has been my general go-to knife for life in the backcountry.",
            "author": "Doug Asano",
            "author_image": "shopify://shop_images/doug.png",
            "object_fit": "cover",
            "object_position": "center"
          }
        },
        "testimonial_drkRKa": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "Dig my Kestrel knife. You never notice that you are even carrying it. At G3 Outfitters, we do some backpack hunting and we endorse this fine product. From Alaska to New Mexico's Gila Wilderness, I pack a Kestrel.",
            "author": "H Jay Platt G3outfitters",
            "author_image": "shopify://shop_images/jay.png",
            "object_fit": "cover",
            "object_position": "center"
          }
        },
        "testimonial_tQTUDz": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "I’ve been using my fixed blade mountain caper for years. I processed an entire mule deer buck with it this year.",
            "author": "Andrew Giesler",
