        "testimonial_AxhXVD": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "I wanted to share a photo of my 11 1/2 year old warrior NWT ram. Absolutely fantastic hunt in beautiful country. I used my Kestrel knife to cape for a life sized mount. Your knife stayed sharp and is a joy to carry, perfect for sheep hunting. Thanks!",
            "author": "Tom Oregon",
            "author_image": "shopify://shop_images/oregon.png",
            "object_fit": "cover",
            "object_position": "center"
          }
        },
        "testimonial_UCMqKG": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "I have a pretty fair assortment of premium backpacking knives and the short Ovis is my absolute favorite and go to for 90% of my hunts. The only time I use another knife is just to try something else, but always end up disappointed in other knives and go back to my Ovis.  Since getting it I have used it on every continent except Africa and Antartica to skin and process animals. It holds an edge and is by far the easiest knife to touch up in the field that I have ever used.  ",
            "author": "Chase Newton",
            "author_image": "shopify://shop_images/chase.png",
            "object_fit": "cover",
            "object_position": "center"
          }
        },
        "testimonial_LhgCKH": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "A knife should feel like an extension of your hand and that’s exactly what the Ovis Hunter is. The balance, the size, the Nitro-V steel, everything just works. It slices effortlessly and makes butchering game in the field a dream. I’ve owned plenty of high-end knives, but I always come back to this one. The Ovis Hunter is the knife I trust in the field, at camp, and everywhere in between",
            "author": "Matt Riley, British Columbia Outdoorsman",
            "author_image": "shopify://shop_images/matt.png",
            "object_fit": "cover",
            "object_position": "center"
          }
        },
        "testimonial_8NrFQW": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "I purchased your mountain scalpel and I believe your Ovis hunter without the handle and wrapped in paracord.  Just got back from a mountain goat trip on Kodiak Island and used both knives to skin and debone the goat on the mountain.  They worked excellent and both the guide and the packer were very impressed",
            "author": "Josh from Big Sky Wood Works",
            "author_image": "shopify://shop_images/josh.png",
            "object_fit": "cover",
            "object_position": "center"
          }
        },
        "testimonial_fdEcPR": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "quote": "Ovis Hunter, Scalpel, and Mouflon Skinner did the job yesterday on a late season elk hunt. Everyone kept asking, 'What knives are these?' because they were cutting so well and didn’t need to be resharpened. The new sheath prototype is really nice. it attaches well to my pack and fits perfectly into my bino harness pocket because it's so thin. Thank you!",
            "author": "@flavs",
            "author_image": "shopify://shop_images/flavs.png",
